{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778225127,"nonce":"XmfCraUZR3zWQVGuj4jooSB8N5c=","message":"## Riccati flavor-(b) S-procedure extension lands; flavor-(a) interpretation refined\n\nFollowing from comments #1–#3 above (the original flavor-(a) finding from `test_cs_faithful_qr_velocity_inflation` xfail, Δv = -0.04% on C\u0026S plant): issue `97c227a` is now implemented on branch `feature/riccati-bw-flavor-b`.\n\n**Headline:** the production Riccati `B_w` is **confirmed** to be flavor-(a) — but the simplest analytic flavor-(b) lift (S-procedure / quadratic-stability) is itself *not enough* to recover C\u0026S's \"Δv \u003e 0\" claim on the C\u0026S plant. Δv stays ≤ 0 across all reasonable Frobenius budgets η ∈ [0, 100]; γ\\*^(b) on rlrmp regime = 0.009618 at η=0.1 (flavor-(a) was 0.009427, ratio 1.02), on C\u0026S regime = 5.898 essentially independent of η ≤ 1.\n\n**Mechanism:** the S-procedure augments Q by `(m·η)^2 · C_q^T · C_q`, penalising [pos, vel] state energy. This always *damps* the controller (lower forward velocity), making it more conservative — opposite of the C\u0026S \"stiffer feedback / faster reach\" signature.\n\n**Refinement of the flavor-(a) ⊊ (b) thesis:** the C\u0026S signature requires more than the quadratic-stability lift. Two candidates deferred to future work (filing follow-up issues): (i) μ-synthesis / structured-singular-value treatment exploiting ΔA's multiplicative structure, (ii) trajectory-coupled time-varying B_w(x_t) finite-horizon DRE along a nominal closed-loop reach.\n\n**Cross-comparison to empirical γ_sd:** deferred — sibling worktrees `feature/induced-gain-flavor-b` and `feature/part2_5-flavor-b-runs` are still in flight. Once empirical γ_sd from flavor-B-trained controllers is available, the comparison `γ\\*^(b) vs γ_sd` will be the strongest single piece of evidence on whether quadratic-stability is the right analytic anchor or whether the empirical training also overshoots into the conservative regime.\n\nSubstantive results table, mechanism analysis, and methodological caveats live on `97c227a` (this comment is the cross-cutting cross-ref per the worked-example protocol in CLAUDE.md).","files":null}]}